Workshop | International Summer Academy in Engineering for Women

ISAE4W International Summer Academy in Engineering for Women

ISAE4W - International Summer Academy in Engineering 4 Women 9th - 24th July 2019

For the 6th time the University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria offers a unique opportunity for a selected group of highly-motivated and talented women (high school, college or undergraduate students) to experience top-class and challenging university-level coursework.

Get some insights into the ISAE4W Class of 2018

Programme

The Academyâs intensive, two and a half week programme combines sophisticated theory with hands-on practical experience in engineering and natural sciences. Besides knowledge transfer in these fields, social, cross-cultural and gender aspects were covered and discussed during lectures and workshops.

In addition to the general programme, each participant can choose one of the two specializations, which will be scheduled for approximately two days:

  • Natural Sciences
  • Engineering and Technology

Natural Sciences

  • Developments in medical technology regarding materials and prosthetic design and control
  • Synthetic biology: promises and dangers for society
  • Molecular biology: forensic DNA profiling and its computational analysis

Engineering and Technology

  • Physics of ferromagnetic materials and their application in technology
  • From conventional magnetism to a railgun
  • Special high voltage applications in modern day technology

Additional lectures, laboratories and seminars cover the following specific issues and current trends:

Applied Sciences in Theory and Practice

  • Group project: cutting-edge technologies and their impact on society
  • Sustainability: the interconnections of different technological systems and considerations about how changes affect these systems
  • Intercultural communication
  • Innovation management â from the first idea to a business plan to the marketing of a final product

Women in Engineering

  • The role of women in science and research
  • Science World CafÃ©: successful scientists from the FH Upper Austria report from their careers and research projects

Interesting Places to Visit

  • Companies: Visit to Rosenbauer, a manufacturer of systems for firefighting and disaster protection
  • Museums: Ars Electronica Center â museum for information technology and technological advancements in society
  • Cultural highlights in Upper Austria: Pflasterspektakel â street performance festival in Linz

Project
In addition, the participants have an ongoing project throughout the entire academy. The project encompass scientific and technological aspects as well as creativity and social impact.

A team of highly qualified academic staff from our university as well as from other universities and organisations provide scientific and technical background on workshop topics and information about the role of women in science and their opportunities in scientific careers.

Why participate?

  • Broaden technical & scientific knowledge
  • Explore the impact of technology on our society in the future
  • Earn academic credit (4 ECTS)
  • Improve language und intercultural skills
  • Make friends from all over the world
  • Creativity, fun and experience
  • Explore (Upper) Austria

Essential Information

  • Target group: women from 18 to 25
  • Language of instruction: English
  • Venue: University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria, Wels, Austria | Europe
  • Fees: â¬ 780,- including tuition fees, room for the entire stay, meals on weekdays (weekends are free for individual activities), numerous field trips

Application

Application: Please send an e-mail to isae4w@fh-ooe.at. You will then receive a personalized registration link to our online application portal (application deadline: 30th April 2019)

Please note that due to limited capacities a maximum of two students per specialization and a total of four students per institution can be accepted. Acceptance decisions will be made exclusively based on the studentsâ qualifications and the fit with the offered specialization. Competitive entry: We reserve the right to decline applicants.

Applicants will be notified about the outcome of the review and selection-process by End of May 2019.

Please note that it is the studentâs obligation to take care of visa arrangements for entry and the duration of their stay in Austria. For information about the visa requirements check the OeAD website https://oead.at/en/to-austria/entry-and-residence

    Summer School in Collaborative Systems and Security

    8 - 14 July 2019

    The Summer School will be held 8 - 14 July 2019 at our School of Informatics, Communications and Media in Hagenberg.

    This Summer School gives you an excellent opportunity to enhance your knowledge and at the same time explore Upper Austria, meet new people, and expand your network internationally. You can earn 4 ECTS for this summer school.

    We are inviting Master's and PhD students with a Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Human-Computer Interaction, Media Informatics and related fields to join us for this international event!
    Students from partner institutions are free of charge! Students who are not from a partner university have to pay a tuition fee in the amount of 350â¬.

    All students have to bear the costs for housing and travelling costs.

    In addition to lectures, workshops and laboratory tutorials, our programme will include site visits and two days filled with social and cultural activities.

      HochschülerInnenschaft der FH OÖ

      Wer sind wir und was sind unsere Tätigkeiten?

      Als eure HochschülerInnenschaft der Fachhochschule Oberösterreich sind wir immer bestrebt, euren Anliegen volle Aufmerksamkeit zu schenken. Jeder Studierende, welcher den ÖH Beitrag bezahlt, ist Mitglied bei uns und hat dadurch Anspruch auf unsere Leistungen. Um uns besser kennenzulernen und damit ihr die richtige Ansprechperson finden könnt, möchten wir uns bei euch vorstellen.

      Unsere ehrenamtlichen Studierenden setzen sich neben ihrem Studium an der FH Oberösterreich für dich ein. Da wir dadurch viel über den Studierendenalltag wissen, können wir umso besser eine Schnittstelle zwischen den Studierenden und der FH Oberösterreich herstellen. Jedoch sind wir nicht Teil der FH, sondern bilden die Interessensvertretung der Studierenden der FH Oberösterreich, welche sich für euch gegenüber der FH einsetzt.

      ÃH FH OÃ Team

      Lerne unser Team kennen

      Eure Ansprechpersonen am Campus

      Ob in Hagenberg, Linz, Steyr oder Wels, unsere Campusteams haben immer ein offenes Ohr für eure Anliegen. Gemeinsam mit den CampusreferentInnen stehen sie euch tagtäglich für Fragen zur Verfügung und kümmern sich obendrein um verschiedenste Veranstaltungen am Campus. Zusätzlich haben wir auf jedem Campus einen Vertrauensstudenten bzw. eine Vertrauensstudentin, die euch bei Sorgen, Ängsten und Zweifeln im Studienalltag helfen.

      Hagenberg

      Campusteam Hagenberg

      Linz

      Campusteam Linz

      Steyr

      Campusteam Steyr

      Wels

      Campusteam Wels

      Referate

      Unsere Referate vertreten relevante Themen in der ÖH. Studierende haben somit zu verschiedenen Themenbereichen Ansprechpersonen, welche für ihre Anliegen da sind. Wenn ihr also Anliegen habt, mit denen wir euch weiterhelfen können, könnt ihr uns jederzeit kontaktieren.

      Sozialreferat

      Bei Fragen zu Beihilfen oder Studiengebühren ist unser Sozialreferat die richtige Anlaufstelle. Ihr könnt dieses Referat ebenfalls aufsuchen, wenn ihr mehr über verschiedenste Beratungsangebote wissen wollt.

      Sozialreferat

      Bildungspolitisches

      Referat

      Unser bildungspolitisches Referat kümmert sich um Anliegen, bei welchen ihr auch rechtliche Beratung braucht. Das heißt, wenn ihr Probleme an der FH haben solltet, könnt ihr euch hier melden.

      Bildungspolitisches Referat

      Wirtschafts-referat

      Das Wirtschaftsreferat behält den Überblick über alle Budgets und Ausgaben der ÖH. Zusätzlich ist

      dieses Referat für die Verwaltung der verschiedenen Budgets

      zuständig.

      Wirtschaftsreferat

      Redaktion

      Unsere Redaktion kümmert sich um einen gefüllten ÖH Blog. Solltet ihr also eine gute Idee für einen Artikel haben, könnt ihr euch jederzeit hier melden und eure schriftstellerischen Fähigkeiten unter Beweis stellen.

      International Staff Training Week FH Upper Austria

      We would be happy to welcome you to our next Staff Training Week, which is preliminarily scheduled for spring 2020.

      The fourth International Staff Training Week is succesfully completed. It lasted for four excellent days, from 24 till 27 April 2018 and it consisted of target group specific workshops, discussions as well as an (optional) cultural visit. The target groups were:

      >> Research & Development

      >> Study Programme Administration

      >> Marketing

      >> International Relations

      There is no fee for the Staff Training Week (only for the cultural excursion, depending on the amount of participants). However, participants are expected to cover their travel and accommodation expenses if they join us in Austria. We always encourage European participants to apply for a financial support through Erasmus+ at their home institutions, and we gladly support with all the necessary documentation .

      If this kind of event attracts your attention and in case you have any questions regarding the event, please don't hesitate to contact us at international@fh-wels.at.

      Contact

      International Office Wels Campus
      University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria
      Stelzhamerstr. 23
      4600 Wels/Austria
      Tel.: +43 5 0804 43140
      E-Mail: international@fh-wels.at

      International Foundation Programme Pathway to Studies in Upper Austria

      A Route into an Austrian Degree

       

      You want to apply for a study programme in Engineering or Business at the University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria but still missing pre-requisites to study?

       

      We have the perfect solution for you! The International Foundation Programme offers you a focused and tailored preparation for your application to study at the FH Upper Austria.

      The main target group are students who wish to study the English-taught Bachelor's programmes in Electrical Engineering or Global Sales and Marketing.

      Perfect for students whoâ¦

      • are looking for a preparation programme taught in English
      • miss sufficient credits in Mathematics, Physics and English to be enrolled in a study programme
      • wish to fresh up Mathematics, Physics and English prior to entering a study programme
      • do not meet entry requirements for studying in Austria
      • wish to brush up their language skills and technical terminology
      • want to learn or improve German


      After completion of the programme, you are well-prepared for commencing your studies at the University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria. Please note: you will not be automatically accepted but need to apply again for the programme of your choice.

      Curriculum

      Mathematics - 8 semester hours per week (8 SWS)

      • Sets of numbers; equations and inequations; linear algebra and geometry; trigonometry and trigonometric functions; complex numbers
      • Sequences and series; basic concepts of differential calculus and integral calculus; linear algebra (particularly vectors) and   geometry; algebraic structures; introduction to probability calculations, statistics

      Physics - 2 semester hours per week (2 SWS)

      • Units, Basics of Mechanics: Kinematics, Dynamics, Work and Energy, Statics, Torque
      • Thermodynamics, Heat and Energy, Ideal Gas, Electricity, Magnetism, Optics, Oscillations and Waves

      English - 2 semester hours per week (2 SWS)

      • Morphology and syntax, oral and written expression of technical issues (with and without use of a dictionary), verbal skills (describe, explain, and present technical issues), writing skills (translate, summarize, prepare papers, ...)

      German as a Foreign Language - 2 to 4 semester hours per week (2-4 SWS)

      • Participation in the A1/A2/B1/B2 (depending on level of skills) language courses

      Additional modules - 1 semester hour per week (1st semester)

      • Intercultural and social competencies

      Essential Information

      Duration of Studies

      • 2 semesters  

        • 1-semester - end of September - beginning of February
        • 2-semester - end of February - beginning of July

      Costs:

      • programme fee: EUR 3600/year

      Please note: accommodation, travel and living cost to/in Austria are not included in this tuition fee.

      Entry Requirements

      • A-Level / High School Diploma or equivalent
        (If the Austrian Higher Education Entrance Qualification is not yet met, the required level can be acquired within the International Foundation Programme. In general, A-level is required, but in some cases excellent performance in AS-level and GCSE-level courses might qualify as well)
      • good English language skills
        English Language Certificate B2 (IELTS, Toefl,...)

      Application

      • Please apply online
      • Application deadline:
        • extended deadline for EU Applicants - August 31,  2019  (original deadline April 30)

      • Required documents:

        • School-leaving Certificate *
        • Certificates from the highest educational level (diplomas, transcript,...)*
        • Birth Certificate
        • photocopy of your passport
        • Motivation Letter
        • CV
        • good knowledge in English Language B2  (Certificates like Ielts, Toefl,Cambridge,...)
        • optional: German Language Certificates (ÃSD, GÃ¶the,...)

        * Foreign documents have to show the necessary legislation and must be translated to German or English. Find all legalisation instructions here.

      • Application procedure:

        • online application
        • formal check of prerequisites
        • compulsory skype interview
